-- Aquarius Plunges in Johannesburg After Government Directive Limits Mining
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-07-19T07:10:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/aquarius-plunges-in-johannesburg-after-government-directive-limits-mining.html

          
          
             Aquarius Platinum Ltd. fell in
Johannesburg trading after the government issued a safety
directive that limits how much the company can mine.  
 Aquarius fell as much as 24 percent to 26 rand and traded
at 26.27 rand as of 9:10 a.m. local time.  
          
          


  


        